'''Machine set up for CNN image classification:
Currently, this is copy and paste only - need to make this a zsh script'''

Resources:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/34097988/how-do-i-install-keras-and-theano-in-anaconda-python-on-windows
https://medium.com/towards-data-science/how-to-set-up-a-deep-learning-environment-on-aws-with-keras-theano-b0f39e3d861c

'''Using Pillow and OpenCV for image manipulation.'''
http://python-guide-pt-br.readthedocs.io/en/latest/scenarios/imaging/

'''Support packages for Pillow'''
https://pillow.readthedocs.io/en/3.0.0/installation.html

# for PNG file access:
conda install zlib

pip install littlecms
pip install Pillow

# install Torch
git clone https://github.com/torch/distro.git ~/torch --recursive
cd ~/torch; bash install-deps;
./install.sh

# Update conda
conda update conda
conda update --all

# Update Theano
pip install --upgrade --no-deps git+git://github.com/Theano/Theano.git

#Update keras
pip install git+git://github.com/fchollet/keras.git
